n]], American lawyer and politician, 37th [[Governor of Nebraska]]\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Taj Mahal (musician)|Taj Mahal]], American blues singer-songwriter and musician\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[Sirajuddin of Perlis]], Yang di-Pertuan Agong of Malaysia\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Johnny Warren]], Australian footballer, coach, and sportscaster (d. 2004)\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[Jesse Winchester]], American singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer (d. 2014)\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[B.S. Chandrasekhar]], Indian cricketer\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Tony Roche]], Australian tennis player and coach\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Udo Lindenberg]], German singer-songwriter and drummer \n*  1947   &ndash; [[Stephen Platten]], English bishop\n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Dick Gaughan]], Scottish singer-songwriter and guitarist\n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[Bill Bruford]], English drummer, songwriter, and producer \n*  1949   &ndash; [[Keith (singer)|Keith]], American pop singer\n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Howard Ashman]], American playwright and composer (d. 1991)\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Keith Bradley, Baron Bradley]], English accountant and politician\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Janez Drnov\u0161ek]], Slovenian economist and politician, 2nd [[President of Slovenia]] (d. 2008)\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Alan Johnson]], English politician, [[Shadow Chancellor of the Exchequer]]\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Valeriya Novodvorskaya]], Russian journalist and politician (d. 2014)\n*[[1951]] &ndash; [[Simon Hughes]], English lawyer and politician\n*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Howard Hampton]], Canadian lawyer and politician\n*[[1954]] &ndash; [[Michael Roberts (jockey)|Michael Roberts]], South African-English jockey\n*[[1955]] &ndash; [[Bill Paxton]], American actor and director (d. 2017)\n*  1955   &ndash; [[David Townsend (musician)|David Townsend]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (d. 2005)\n*[[1956]] &ndash; [[Sugar Ray Leonard]], American boxer \n*  1956   &ndash; [[Annise Parker]], American politician\n*  1956   &ndash; [[Bob Saget]], American comedian, actor